item.title: CVE-2011-4182|2024-09-17T02:57:38.708Z -- suse%20linux%20enterprise -- sysconfig
item.description: Missing escaping of ESSID values in sysconfig of SUSE Linux Enterprise allows attackers controlling an access point to cause execute arbitrary code. Affected releases are sysconfig prior to 0.83.7-2.1.
